{
  "texts": [
    "Subsequently, three distinct machine learning classifiers -random forest, support vector classifier (SVC), and AdaBoost-were trained using the extracted features to automate the detection of dysgraphia.",
    "The outcomes of this study reveal that random forest outperformed the other classifiers, demonstrating superior classification performance.In [59], a digital system for dysgraphia identification is proposed.",
    "It utilizes a Wacom tablet with an interactive stylus for data collection as students perform five handwriting tasks.",
    "Key metrics like total time, tip pressure, and pen coordinates are recorded.",
    "Nine distinct features including on-paper segments, in-air segments, total time, total airtime, total time spent on paper, mean pressure, the velocity of the pen, etc. are extracted."
  ]
}